      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A serious public discourse about climate change policy has yet to develop in the United States. I hope that we begin such a dialogue soon and allow all those with relevant information to share their ideas openly.</p>
        <p>It concerns me deeply that the administration believes that policy decisions should be decided by a select few and disseminated to the public rather than engaging the public with a real dialogue in which the views of the government's well-informed scientists are freely expressed.</p>
        <p>An issue as complex as climate change requires many perspectives, including that of the scientific community.</p>
        <p>Ryan Hinrichs  Bronxville, N.Y., Jan. 31, 2006</p>
        <p>The writer is a chemistry professor at Sarah Lawrence College.</p>
      </block>
